{"sections":[{"chapter":"Import of the Swift Package and choose its librairies","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework."}]}],"title":"Swift Package integration","image":"ic_unified_ds.png","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26","kind":"hero","estimatedTimeInMinutes":10,"backgroundImage":"ic_unified_ds.png"},{"tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode.","type":"text"}]}]}],"title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries","anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","stepsSection":[{"code":null,"media":"tutorial-1-ouds-swift-package.png","type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Xcode, in your "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"project package dependencies"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":", add a new "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"dependency"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Search with the GitHub repository URL (https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios), and select the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ouds-ios"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" dependency."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can then choose the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"dependency rule"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" you want."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To know which version you need, you can have a look on the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and also the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"caption":[],"runtimePreview":null},{"code":null,"media":"tutorial-1-ouds-libraries.png","type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"They can be embeded inside your "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"target"}]},{"type":"text","text":" librairies."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesContract"}]},{"type":"text","text":" library provides the main elements like the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":". The theme contract is defined inside it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesOrange"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesSosh"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesWireframe"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSComponents","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensRaw"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensComponents","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSModules"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSFoundations","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic."}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSSwiftUI"}]}]}],"runtimePreview":null}]}],"kind":"tasks"},{"assessments":[{"content":[],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Which of these choices is correct?","type":"text"}]}],"choices":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay."}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS and visionOS. tvOS, watchOS and CarPlay are not scoped yet."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides UIKit components","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports officialy only SwiftUI. UIKit is very experimental and not recommended.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"multiple-choice"},{"content":[],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?","type":"text"}]}],"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the "},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" product wraps all of them."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"multiple-choice"}],"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessments"},{"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","title":"Instanciate and inject a theme","kind":"callToAction","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The theme is exposed as one object which will be injected inside your SwiftUI view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The theme provides all tokens which defines in the end the rendering of everything."}],"action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme","overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"isActive":true}}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"modules":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Preparation-of-the-theme","projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment